[PLAN  ] -------- design plan --------
  summary: A 30-degree tilted laptop tray with a vertical VESA mounting plate, diagonal support struts, thickened gusset junctions, hexagonal airflow cutouts, and stress-relief fillets/chamfers, designed to print flat within a 256mm build volume.
  size:    [240.0, 180.0, 140.0] mm
  comp 1: vesa_plate [base] box(length=120.0, width=5.0, height=140.0) — Vertical backplate for monitor attachment, provides primary mounting interface
  comp 2: tray_base [union] box(length=240.0, width=200.0, height=5.0) — Main laptop resting surface, tilted 30 degrees downward toward the user
  comp 3: tray_front_lip [union] box(length=240.0, width=5.0, height=15.0) — Front retention wall to prevent laptop from sliding off the tilted surface
  comp 4: tray_side_lip_left [union] box(length=5.0, width=200.0, height=10.0) — Left containment wall to prevent lateral sliding
  comp 5: tray_side_lip_right [union] box(length=5.0, width=200.0, height=10.0) — Right containment wall to prevent lateral sliding
  comp 6: support_strut_left [union] box(length=20.0, width=90.0, height=5.0) — Diagonal brace transferring tray load to the VESA plate
  comp 7: support_strut_right [union] box(length=20.0, width=90.0, height=5.0) — Diagonal brace transferring tray load to the VESA plate
  comp 8: gusset_left [union] box(length=20.0, width=20.0, height=5.0) — Triangular thickened junction reinforcing strut-to-tray connection
  comp 9: gusset_right [union] box(length=20.0, width=20.0, height=5.0) — Triangular thickened junction reinforcing strut-to-tray connection
  comp 10: vesa_mount_holes [cut] cylinder(length=5.5, width=5.5, height=10.0) — Four clearance holes for M4 screws in a 75x75mm VESA pattern
  comp 11: tray_hex_cutouts [cut] custom(length=15.0, width=15.0, height=8.0) — Pattern of hexagonal holes to reduce material weight and improve airflow
  comp 12: tray_corner_fillets [fillet] custom(length=3.0, width=3.0, height=3.0) — Radius fillets on tray outer edges to reduce stress concentrations
  comp 13: vesa_edge_chamfers [chamfer] custom(length=2.0, width=2.0, height=2.0) — Chamfers on VESA plate top and bottom edges for safety and print quality
  features:
    * Vertical VESA mounting plate with 75x75mm hole pattern
    * 30-degree downward tilted tray surface
    * Front and side retention lips
    * Two diagonal support struts connecting plate to tray
    * Thickened gusset junctions at strut-tray interfaces
    * Hexagonal cutout pattern in tray center
    * Filleted tray corners and chamfered VESA edges
  assumptions:
    * Laptop footprint fits within 230x190mm, leaving 5mm clearance on tray edges
    * M4 screws used for VESA mounting, requiring 5.5mm clearance holes
    * PLA material with 0.2mm layer height and 20% infill for structural parts
  risks:
    * Hex cutout pattern may weaken tray if spacing is too tight; mitigation: maintain 15mm minimum wall between holes
    * Strut attachment points may experience high bending stress; mitigation: gussets and 5mm base thickness distribute load
    * Fillets on rotated geometry can cause boolean errors in CadQuery; mitigation: apply fillets after all unions are complete
